        • timer

          javax.swing.Timer timer
          we NEED timers to start the whole thing, because if we do it inside the constructor the progressBar will be on 100% when we open it up ^^ . because all gui work is threadsafe until the setVisible(true). and even if we make the calls after the setVisible(true) - the methods called after is aparently still not shown until the constructor is done doing it's work .. thats why we have a timer to kick the whole thing into motion.
